The paper proposes a new architecture for recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to address the problem of vanishing gradients and improve the capture of long-temporal dependencies. This is a common problem in machine learning, particularly in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
